cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR

The paper focuses on machine learning at the edge of wireless networks, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses the training of on-device ML models. The second likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper focuses on wireless networks and communication-efficient distributed ML frameworks. The third likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper discusses distributed ML frameworks. The fourth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper discusses mission-critical intelligent systems. The fifth likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper discusses privacy-preserving distributed ML frameworks.
